name: Mould and Sacrificial formwork Dimensions are within Shop Drawings Tolerance
Stitch pour Reinforcement lapping bars spacing maintained and template plate installed
Detailed inspection of Mould and cage
Condeck (Top Slab) - Verify all brackets fixed at slab thickening
All Stainless Steel Ferrules are installed in accordance with Drawings
All Stainless Items are installed in accordance with Drawings
Earthing and Bonding is installed in accordance with Drawings
100mm long 6mm fillet welds between bars/ 55mm long butt welds
All Temperature Loggers are installed as per Approved WMS
Ensure All temperature Loggers are Working (Check Maturix)
All Cooling tubes installed as per drawings
Slump within Allowable Tolerance (180+/-40) (Tested 1st truck and subsequently for every 20m3)

Concrete Placed within allowable time from Batching Plant
No Free Fall During Pour (not more than 2 metres from ground)

Retarders applied on Green Cut areas as shown in drawings
Concrete Cylinders Crushed and Checked for stripping strength
Lifting strength required for stage 2 casting - 45MPa
Specify strength at time of lifting
Tarped until the curing strength achieved
Lifted and Handled as per Drawings
Storage as per Approved Temporary Works Drawings
Secondary Curing as per Approved Methodology
Product Dimensions Achieved and are within Specified Tolerance
Cast-in Items are all in Place and within Specified Tolerance
Temperature Logging Completed and Conforming. Attach Results
Repairs Completed as per approved WMS (if applicable)
NCR Approved by Client and Repairs Completed (if applicable)
As-Built Drawings Completed, Stamped and Attached
